# Navbar auth state

Marketing navbars (`LandingNavbar`, `Navbar`) must **not** hard-code a static "Sign in" link.

## Required pattern
- Use shared `NavAuthActions` from `components/foundation/navigation/NavAuthActions.tsx`.
- Read session via `useAuth()` (`isAuthenticated`, `isLoading`, `user`, `signOut`).
- **Signed out**: show "Sign in" → `/sign-in`.
- **Signed in**: show account menu (avatar + name) with Dashboard + Sign out — never show "Sign in".

## AuthContext
- `isAuthenticated` is `true` only after `/api/auth/session` returns a user (401 → `false`).
- Do not infer auth from the default `Demo User` placeholder.

## Layouts
- Desktop: `NavAuthActions layout="inline"`.
- Mobile drawer: `NavAuthActions layout="mobile" onNavigate={closeMenu}`.

Dashboard workspace chrome (`WorkspaceSolutionChrome`, sidebar) is separate; marketing pages still need `NavAuthActions` so users stay signed in visually when browsing `/`, `/marketplace`, `/contact`.
